Text: The next day...
Heheheh... You actually dared to show up.
You're the challengers from yesterday...!

You really did a number on us yesterday! And you
even had the nerve to school us like that...
Our pride is in tatters!
How are you going to make up for it, huh?!
Isn't it natural to defeat any challengers?

That attitude... But it won't last long. How long
can you withstand all of us?
...Fine, bring it on. All of you.
Heheh. Don't mind if we do! Hraaaaghh!
Haaah! Hyaaaaah!
This is nothing... No need to even use my sword!
Damn her! She's dodging everything...!

Don't let her scare you! Just keep attacking!
She'll tire out soon enough!
I see... Right, let's wear her down!

(They've thought things through... With their numbers
advantage, I'll lose once I run out of stamina...
In that case!)
Take this!
...Minimal moves are enough. Evade...and strike!
S-She dodged it again... Guargh?!
Now's our chance!
What the...?!
(They managed to get behind me?! I can't dodge—)
Huh...?
How did you managed to dodge that?!

Just now...did my body stopped right before the
attack...?

(That move...was just like Mundane's. Did I
unconsciously mimic him?)
(No, that's not it. What I just did was—)

Wh-What's up with her moves... Aren't they different
from yesterday? They're more mundane, more normal...

(...Not imitating. My movements may be mundane and
normal, but they're optimal and minimal... That's
what I've been subconsciously aiming for.)

(Beyond this elevated art form, no doubt, lies that
sword I seek! In that case, I...)
I will pave my own path to that sword!
Urrghh?!
I-Impossible...
You're the last one.
I-I won't go down that easily! Hyaaaah!
...An opening! Hah!
Aghh...!
It's over.
I think I'm starting to glimpse the world he sees...
The next day...

Well, time to say goodbye to this town. I see my
path now. Maybe it's time for some mountain
training?
Wait! Please wait!
Aren't you one of the guys from yesterday...?
Ah, they're the challengers you defeated.

Too bad about yesterday. I would've paid good money
to see one of the former members of Velgalta's Seven
Blades lose.
...You were there? I didn't notice at all...

Hmph... No surprise. I completely masked my
presence.
You can do that...? I'm impressed!

I'd chalk that more down to your skills of
perception than my abilities...but never mind. It
seems they have something they want to say to you.
What is it? Coming to challenge me again?

O-Of course not! After crossing swords with you,
we've tasted just how powerless we are!

Yeah. And...we all fell in love with your sword
technique! So...

Please make us your disciples... No, in fact, we beg
you to take us on as your disciples!
Huh...?

We know it's a lot to ask, but please! Stay in town
and train us!
W-Wait! Are you serious?

Of course we're serious! We never knew such
beautiful, strong swordplay existed!
So, what will you do?
(My swordplay moved them like Mundane's moved me...)
...I'm flattered and honored by the sentiment.
But I'm still in training. I can't teach others.

In fact, I've just decided to start from scratch
again. So, I'm sorry, but I can't be your master.
B-But...!

That said, I know someone who could be. Someone with
an eye to discern true skill.

...Hey, what're you looking at me for? You're not
suggesting—
Yes, I am. How about Goldy Gilded over here?

I've heard of him. Goldy Gilded the Unbeaten
Legend...!

Goldy Gilded...the Victorious Golden Dragon! I never
would've dreamed of being taught by him...!
Master Goldy! Please guide us!
...Hmm, has a nice ring to it.

Very well! I, Goldy Gilded, will lead you to greater
heights!!
Master Goldy!!!
Heheh. It actually might be your true calling.

As for me, I'll continue on my own path and someday
catch up with Mundane.
...Just you wait.

With those words, Annerose Nichtsehen renews her
resolve and continues her journey.
